The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Mesa Vista had a population of 217. The population density was {{convert|44.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Mesa Vista was 80.6% [[White Americans|White]], 0.5% [[African Americans|African American]], 1.4% [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0.0% [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0.0% [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 0.0% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 17.5% from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 8.3% of the population.

There were 89 households, out of which 25.8% included children under the age of 18, 55.1% were married-couple households, 11.2% were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 20.2% had a female householder with no partner present, and 13.5% had a male householder with no partner present. 21.3% of households were one person, and 12.4% were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.44. There were 63 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (70.8% of all households).

The age distribution was 11.5% under the age of 18, 0.5% aged 18 to 24, 21.2% aged 25 to 44, 37.3% aged 45 to 64, and 29.5% who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 55.5{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 100.9 males.

There were 106 housing units at an average density of {{convert|21.7|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 89 (84.0%) were occupied. Of these, 91.0% were owner-occupied, and 9.0% were occupied by renters.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mesa Vista CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0647086 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=March 26, 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Mesa Vista CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0647086 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=March 26, 2025}}</ref>

